8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 821, L.D. 1246, “Resolve, Directing the
10 Department of Economic and Community Development to Convene a Working Group to
11 Review the Process of Setting Impact Fees”
12 Amend the resolve by inserting after the title the following:
13 'Emergency preamble. Whereas, acts and resolves of the Legislature do not
14 become effective until 90 days after adjournment unless enacted as emergencies; and
15 Whereas, the State is facing a housing crisis that harms the quality of life and
16 economic prosperity of all Maine residents that needs to be addressed as soon as possible;
17 and
18 Whereas, to address this crisis, an additional 84,000 new housing units must be built
19 by 2030; and
20 Whereas, a study on the barriers to addressing this crisis, completed in January 2025
21 by HR&A Advisors, found that unpredictable and overly burdensome costs and fees,
22 including impact fees, were a deterrent to the construction of housing; and
23 Whereas, the HR&A Advisors report recommends the State establish a working
24 group to review current local fees, including impact fees, and develop standards by which
25 a municipality determines the local infrastructure costs and impact fees resulting from a
26 housing development project, a transparent process by which municipalities establish those
27 fees and a requirement that the fees be established at the beginning of the project approval
28 process; and
29 Whereas, in the judgment of the Legislature, these facts create an emergency within
30 the meaning of the Constitution of Maine and require the following legislation as
31 immediately necessary for the preservation of the public peace, health and safety; now,
32 therefore, be it'
33 Amend the resolve in section 1 in the 3rd line (page 1, line 3 in L.D.) by inserting after
34 the following: "Development," the following: 'as the state agency responsible for
