COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 821, L.D. 1246
315 overseeing the Housing Opportunity Program established in the Maine Revised Statutes,
326 Title 5, section 13056-J, or a successor agency,'
3 Amend the resolve in section 1 in the 3rd line (page 1, line 3 in L.D.) by inserting after
4 the following: "Future" the following: 'and the Maine Office of Community Affairs'
5 Amend the resolve in section 1 in the 5th line (page 1, line 5 in L.D.) by striking out
6 the following: "the Maine Revised Statutes,"
7 Amend the resolve in section 1 in the 12th line (page 1, line 12 in L.D.) by striking out
8 the following: "department" and inserting the following: 'state agency responsible for
9 overseeing the Housing Opportunity Program'
10 Amend the resolve by inserting before the summary the following:
11 'Emergency clause. In view of the emergency cited in the preamble, this legislation
12 takes effect when approved.'
13 Amend the resolve by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
14 section number to read consecutively.
15 SUMMARY
1166 This amendment adds an emergency preamble and emergency clause to the resolve.
1177 The amendment adds the Maine Office of Community Affairs as a participant in the study
1188 under the resolve and clarifies the state agency responsible for overseeing the Housing
1199 Opportunity Program, currently established within the Department of Economic and
2200 Community Development, is the agency responsible for submitting a report to the Joint
2211 Standing Committee on Housing and Economic Development.
